{
  "description": "A dramatic view of a tall waterfall cascading down a steep, rocky cliff face. The waterfall appears powerful, creating a misty spray at its base and a turbulent flow in the river below. The cliff is composed of dark gray rock, with lighter patches where the water has worn away the surface. Large boulders and smaller rocks litter the area at the base of the falls, forming a rough, uneven landscape. A fallen tree trunk lies in the foreground, adding a sense of scale and natural texture. A tiny figure, possibly a person, can be seen at the bottom right, providing scale to the massive waterfall and landscape. The overall impression is one of immense natural power and rugged beauty.",
